## Development Rules

1. Mobile-first approach: design for 375px then enhance to 768px and 1024px
2. Accessibility is required: WCAG 2.1 AA keyboard navigation ARIA labels
3. Use component classes from index.css NOT heavy inline Tailwind
4. Conventional commits: feat: fix: style: refactor: docs: chore:
5. Test on mobile after building each component
6. Use PropTypes for all components
7. Create index.js in component folders for clean imports
8. Never commit .env.local or API keys
9. Always validate form inputs before API calls
10. Show loading states during API calls
11. Show clear error messages on failures
12. Show success confirmations on success

## Tailwind v4 Critical Rules

Use @import "tailwindcss" NOT @tailwind base/components/utilities
Theme config in CSS with @theme directive NOT in tailwind.config.js
Avoid @apply - write CSS directly using CSS variables
Component classes go in @layer components block

## Git Workflow

main branch is production - always deployable
develop branch is integration - test features together
feature/\* branches for new work - always branch from develop
Always create PR from feature to develop then develop to main

